Package ru.nsu.ablaginin

Class Graph<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.nsu.ablaginin.Graph<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of vertex's name, must be Comparable
    public class Graph<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
    Simple graph G = (V, E), where V - list of Vertexes, containing name or just information about vertex, and E - list of Edges kind of (V1, V2, w): - V1 from-vertex - V2 to-vertex - w - weight of the edge (for example a distant between two cities). Simple graph means that for each E1 = (V1, V2, w) and E2 = (V1, V2, w') we have w = w' and E1 = E2.

      • dijkstra

        public java.util.List<Vertex<T>> dijkstra​(T keyStart)
        Dijkstra's algorithm finds the shortest ways to other vertexes from the starting vertex. For each iteration algorithm takes a vertex with the least value and puts its value + edge's weight to adjacent vertex if its value is higher than new one. If adjacent hasn't been visited yet, it adds to the priority queue. Algorithm ends if queue.size() is zero.
        Parameters:
        keyStart - algorithm's starting vertex
        Returns:
        sorted list of the vertex by value
